&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Specialist Speech and Language Therapist - Special &amp; Mainstream Schools - Fixed Term&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers a great opportunity to further develop your skills in supporting children with complex needs and eating and drinking difficulties attending special schools. You will join our highly skilled multi-disciplinary team working in special schools receiving support from a more experienced colleague and working closely with school staff, occupational therapists and physiotherapists. You will also work with a small caseload of children with a range of speech, language and communication needs in mainstream schools as well as contributing to team training initiatives and project work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department offers:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Easy access to specialists in all clinical areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent support systems with personal appraisal, objectives and training plans designed to meet your specific needs/CPD requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designated admin and planning time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Involvement in innovative project work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMelanie AbbaJob titlePrincipal Speech and Language TherapistEmail addressmelanie.abba@nhs.netTelephone number0208 869 3010Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or contact Catherine Sutcliffe Principal Speech and Language Therapist on 0208 869 2473&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
